    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-29T11:47:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-29T11:47:00-05:00" n="663"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d663">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/631</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Dutch-Scandinavian Socialist Committee</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">
                        <persName type="from">Branting</persName>, Chairman;
                            <persName>Huysmans</persName>, Secretary</hi>) <hi rend="italic">to
                        President <persName corresp="#p_WW1" type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d663fn2">Copy received in the Department of State, June
                        2.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-29T17:47:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1917, 5.47 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>American delegates, conference Stockholm, wire passport refused. Our committee
                    hope only misunderstanding, for conference <pb facs="0814" n="740"
                        xml:id="pg_740"/> convoked on principle laid down in your speech Senate.
                    Definite refusal by American Republic would not be understood in democratic
                    countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Branting</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Huysmans</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
